    <!-- Chosen Palette: Focused Calm -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A dashboard-style, tabbed interface is chosen for optimal user experience. It logically segments the report into its natural phases (Strategy, Phase 1, Phase 2, Phase 3) and a dedicated Topic Explorer. This is more intuitive than a long scrolling page, allowing the user to focus on their current preparation stage while keeping other sections easily accessible. Key interactions include tab switching to navigate between phases, an interactive chart to visualize data, and clickable daily cards to reveal detailed study tasks. This structure transforms the static report into a user-centric, task-oriented application. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Paper 1 Subject Weightage -> Goal: Compare -> Viz/Presentation: Doughnut Chart -> Interaction: Hover for details -> Justification: Provides an immediate, engaging visual comparison of subject importance, superior to a static table. Library: Chart.js (Canvas).
        - Report Info: Detailed 40-Day Plan -> Goal: Organize -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive Timeline/Grid of Cards -> Interaction: Click a day card to expand/collapse details -> Justification: Breaks down the dense schedule into manageable daily chunks, preventing information overload and allowing users to focus on the current day's tasks. Method: HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Report Info: High-Yield Topics (Table 3) -> Goal: Organize/Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Interactive Topic Explorer -> Interaction: Select subject from a dropdown to dynamically display relevant topics -> Justification: Creates a focused, user-driven way to explore topics without the clutter of a large, multi-column table. Method: HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Report Info: Core Principles -> Goal: Inform -> Viz/Presentation: Stylized Cards with Icons -> Interaction: Static display -> Justification: Enhances readability and visual appeal of key strategic points. Method: HTML/CSS (Tailwind).
        - Report Info: Requested Trackers/Flashcards -> Goal: Provide Utility -> Viz/Presentation: Download Buttons -> Interaction: Click to generate and download a file -> Justification: Fulfills the user request for printable/digital tools directly within the application. Method: JS File Generation.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
